      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0636P0-02565'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020618_GCR_19' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 52 agreed to
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_118gc' title='Col. 118GC &mdash; HL Deb 18 June 2002 vol 636 c118GC' name='column_118gc' href='#column_118gc' rel='bookmark'>118GC</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0636P0-02566'>
        <a name='S5LV0636P0_20020618_GCR_20'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-shutt' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020618_GCR_20' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Shutt' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-shutt" title="Mr David Shutt">Lord Shutt of Greetland</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            moved Amendment No. 184:
            <q>Before Clause 53, insert the following new clause&#x2014;</q>
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0636P0-02567'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020618_GCR_21' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        "PARTICIPATION AND UNDERSTANDING
        <q><ol>
        <li>(1) Before making any order in respect of a child, the court shall explain to the child the nature of the proceedings and where the child is charged with an offence the nature of the charge.</li>
        <li>(2) The explanation shall be given in simple language suitable to the child's age and understanding."</li>
        </ol></q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0636P0-02568'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020618_GCR_22' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: I am sure that the Committee will give a tremendous welcome to the idea that a child should have the proceedings explained to them, and that the explanation should be made in simple language. It seems to me that clarity and the use of simple language is essential when talking to a child, whether that child is a small child or a more elderly child, as discussed earlier. It is important that the child understands the proceedings and that the explanation is given in simple language. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0636P0-02569'>
