          <p class='first-para'>
            It is expensive. From my fairly recent memory, secure accommodation in England and Wales costs of the order of &#x00A3;125,000 a year. On the other hand, as a number of noble Lords have observed, the alternatives are extremely expensive in social disharmony and real distress caused by quite young children, wholly disproportionate to their chronological age. The funding will have to be made available.
          </p>
