          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-gareth-williams" title="Mr Gareth Williams">Lord Williams of Mostyn</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            It is. The reason is to allow flexibility: if it was more appropriate that the notice be served&#x2014;this concerns only the question of serving a notice&#x2014;by another person, that flexibility should be available. It is only a notice-serving power.</p><p>
            Clause 55, as amended, agreed to.</p><p>
            5.45 p.m.</p><p>
            Clause 56 [<span class="italic">Youth conferences and youth conference plans</span>]:
          </p>
